    # redshift commands
				## NOTE: Yes, the "killall" is necessary for the "x" to work after having done a "t" (time-based warming) command. This is redshift's glitchiness; nothing to do with i3.
				## NOTE: i3 also has a glitch in how it passes things to "exec", requiring us to (if we want to do any "one-shot" any time after the time-based-warmth command) either do "x" command first (even though it's included in the "one-shot commands here!), or include a "sleep 1" command within the "one-shot" command (after the "killall" part), since apparently the actual "one-shot" part gets executed before the "killall" part takes effect.
		bindsym $mod+y mode "redshift"
		mode "redshift" {
